TABULA.

1. Carta Doneeani comitis de Carriek de tribus marchis argenti

de terra de Barrebeth. [ante Aa). 1200]

Original at Panmure. The fragment of a seal of white wax remaina show- ing the head and wing of a griffin ; apparently the same with the seal figured in “ Liber de Melros.'' Pl. vm. fig. 5.

2. Carta J oeelini Episcopi Glasguensis de ecelesia de Kirkebride de Lat-ges ad petitionem Rogeri (16 Sealebroe. [a. 1199]

Original at Panmure. The Bishop's seal remains nearly entire, as en- graved in the Registers of Glasgow and Melros.
